\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Ford
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="center" valignment="top" bottomline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="center" valignment="top" bottomline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="center" valignment="top" bottomline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout
1
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
</lyxtabular>

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We only have set the value for the upper triangular matrix, for the lower
 triangular matrix we will use the reciprocal values of the upper triangular
 matrix based on the following rule 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "teknomoAHPtutorial"

\end_inset

: If 
\begin_inset Formula $a_{ij}$
\end_inset

 is the element of row 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 column 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 of the matrix, then the lower diagonal is filled using this equation: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
a_{ij}=\frac{1}{a_{ij}}\label{eq:reciprocal}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using the rule above we now have the complete comparison matrix in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "tab:Complete-comparison-matrix"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "tab:Complete-comparison-matrix"

\end_inset

